The paper deals with multimodal classification tasks, specifically in the domains of face recognition and target classification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a sparsity-based approach for feature-level fusion, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of a possibilistic weighting scheme for quality-based fusion suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
